use 0805 everywhere possible

VCC = 3.3v
VDDA = 3.3V
V_BATT = battery voltage

AVOID:
there is a tempurature sersor at ADC1_IN16

PC13,14,15 less output current 

review the direction of motor connector in board design

CIN for NCP1117 -- 10uf (typ)
Cout for NCP1117 > 4.7uf (ESR) that is within the limits of 33 m (typ) to 2.2  is required. 

***********************************************************************

Default boot from bank 1(512K)

Bootloader: activate by apply Pattern3
BOOT0--GND
BOOT1--GND
BFB2--in the user option memory

USART1 be used in simple debug situation
PA8--USART1_CK
PA9--USART1_TX
PA10--USART1_RX
PA11--USART1_CTS
PA12--USART1_RTS

CONNECT to JTAG(for advance debug)
NRST--RST
PA13--JT_TMS
PA14--JT_TCK
PA15--JT_TDI
PB3--JT_TDO
PB4--JT_TRST

CONNECT to mpu6050
PB5--I2C1_SMBA
PB8--I2C1_SCL--REMAP
PB9--I2C1_SDA--REMAP
PC12--INT

CONNECT to motor driver
PA1--M1PWM(TIM5_CH2)
PA2--M1I2
PA3--M1I1
PA4--STBY
PA5--M2I1
PA6--M2I2
PA7--M2PWM(TIM3_CH2)

CONNECT to encoder(possible interrupt)
PB6--M1CA(TIM4_CH1)
PB7--M1CB(TIM4_CH2)
PC7--M2CA(TIM3_CH2)
PC6--M2CB(TIM3_CH1)

CONNECT to infarred sensor(Logic Level Converter?)
PC0--IR_IN1
PC1--IR_IN2
PC2--IR_IN3
PC3--IR_IN4
PB15--IR_OUT1
PB14--IR_OUT2
PB13--IR_OUT3
PB12--IR_OUT4

PB10--BUTTON1
PC4--LED1
PC5--LED2